A '''hybrid shipping container''' is a shipping system that uses the energy of [[phase-change material]] (PCM) in combination with the ability to recharge without removing the media. This ability is known as "[[cold-energy battery]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greencooling.co.uk/our-products/cold-batteries/ |title=Cold Batteries |publisher=Green Cooling |date=2014-06-20 |accessdate=2017-01-14}}</ref>

Currently, this technology is only being used in a limited number of shipping containers.

1. SkyCell 770C
2. SkyCell 1500C
3. SkyCell 770CRT
4. SkyCell 1500CRT

A Cold-energy battery works by storing energy to a given temperature and using its thermal mass to maintain this temperature. It can be recharged by being placed in a temperature range applicable to its phase change window.

