n 2011 because "significant portions" of the papers duplicated previously published work.<ref>{{cite news |first=Alicia |last=Rivera |title=Ciencia china 'duplicada' en Galicia |url=http://www.elpais.com/articulo/sociedad/Ciencia/china/duplicada/Galicia/elpepisoc/20110520elpepisoc_8/Tes | publisher=El País | date=May 20, 2011 }}{{cite news |first=Paul |last=Ingendaay |title=War die Guttenberg-Affäre denn zu gar nichts gut?|url=http://www.faz.net/IN/INtemplates/faznet/default.asp?tpl=common/zwischenseite.asp&dx1={B43A6DE1-AB1B-0749-EF51-A4D52091788B}|publisher= Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung |date=June 15, 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |title=Addition/Correction: Prediction of Refractive Index of Polymers Using Artificial Neural Networks |volume=56 |page=688 |date=2010-02-09 |journal= Journal of Chemical & Engineering Data |doi=10.1021/je200071p |issue=3|last1=Astray |first1=G |last2=Cid |first2=A |last3=Moldes |first3=O |last4=Ferreiro-Lage |first4=J. A |last5=GáLvez |first5=J. F |last6=Mejuto |first6=J. C }}{{Cite journal |title=Addition/Correction: Prediction of Prop-2-enoate Polymer and Styrene Polymer Glass Transition Using Artificial Neural Networks |volume=56 |page=689 |date=2010-02-09 |journal= Journal of Chemical & Engineering Data |doi=10.1021/je200072e |issue=3|last1=Astray |first1=G |last2=Cid |first2=A |last3=Ferreiro-Lage |first3=J. A |last4=GáLvez |first4=J. F |last5=Mejuto |first5=J. C |last6=Nieto-Faza |first6=O }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Something rotten in the state of Spain, say whistleblowers|url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/news/something-rotten-in-the-state-of-spain-say-whistleblowers/420782.article|publisher=Times Higher Education|date=2018-08-09|access-date=2018-04-16}}</ref> * [[Leo Paquette#Scientific misconduct|Leo Paquette]] (US), an Ohio State University professor, plagiarized sections from an unfunded NIH grant application for use in his own NIH grant application.<ref name="NIH">{{Citation | title = Final Findings of Scientific Misconduct | author = Office of Research Integrity | date = June 25, 1993 | publisher= DHHS | periodical = Nih Guide | volume = 22 | issue = 23 | url = https://grants.nih.gov/grants/guide/notice-files/not93-177.html | access-date = October 3, 2016 }}</ref> He also plagiarized a NSF proposal for use in one of his scientific publications.<ref name="C&EN-Misconduct">{{cite journal | vauthors = Zurer P | title = NSF, Paquette Settle Misconduct Case | journal = Chemical & Engineering News |volume = 76 | issue = 10 | pages = 25–26 | date = March 9, 1998 | doi= 10.1021/cen-v076n010.p025 }}</ref><ref name="OSU">{{Citation | title = Scientific Misconduct Charge Ruled Valid | last = Gerstner | first = Ruth | date = August 9, 1993 | publisher= Ohio State University | url = https://news.osu.edu/news/1993/08/09/93-08-09_Scientific_Misconduct_Charge_Ruled_Valid/ | access-date = October 3, 2016 }}</ref> * H. Zhong, T. Liu, and their colleagues (China) at [[Jinggangshan University]] have retracted at least 70 papers published in [[Acta Crystallographica]]<ref name="pmid21579903">{{cite journal | vauthors = Zhong H, Duan SH, Hong YP, Li ML, Liu YQ, Luo CJ, Luo QY, Xiao SZ, Xie HL, Xu YP, Yang XM, Zeng XR, Zhong QY | title = Retraction of articles by H. Zhong et al | journal = Acta Crystallographica Section E | volume = 66 | issue = Pt 1 | pages = e11–2 | date = December 2009 | pmid = 21579903 | pmc = 2980006 | doi = 10.1107/S1600536809049964 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Retraction of articles by T. Liu et al. | url = https://journals.iucr.org/e/issues/2010/01/00/me0405/index.html|publisher=International Union of Crystallography|date=2010-01-01|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref> following analyses that revealed the organic structures claimed in these papers to be impossible or implausible; the supporting data appeared to have been taken from valid structures that had then been altered by substituting atoms.<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Harrison WT, Simpson J, Weil M | title